Analyze the current changes and recommend which tests to run.

## Steps

1. Get changed files: `git diff --name-only HEAD` (staged + unstaged)
2. Map each file to a category using the table below
3. Output the recommended command

## File to Category Mapping

<!-- Replace with your project's source paths and test categories -->
| Source path pattern | Category |
|---------------------|----------|
| `*/domain/*` | unit |
| `*/data/*` | integration |
| `*/ui/*` | ALL (no filter) |
| `build.gradle*` | ALL (no filter) |
| Multiple categories | ALL (no filter) |

## Output Format

```
## Test Recommendation

**Changed files:** [list]
**Detected category:** [category]
**Recommended command:** <your-test-command> [-PtestCategory=X]
```

